    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-02-09T16:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-02-09T16:45:00-05:00" n="276"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/4546: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-09T16:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 9, 1927—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. Today brings first train service between Managua and Corinto since
                        Saturday.<note n="33" xml:id="d276fn33">February 5.</note> Passengers report
                    frightful devastation at Chinandega with strong likelihood of another attack by
                    revolutionists on that or neighboring city.<note n="34" xml:id="d276fn34">On
                        February 14 Admiral Latimer was authorized to use the forces under his
                        command to keep open the railroad and to establish neutral zones in such
                        places along the railroad as he deemed “necessary to safeguard the lives and
                        property of American and foreign citizens.” (File No. 817.00/4584.)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
